### ============================================================
### TVA Workshop — API Test File
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension (ms-vscode.rest-client)
### Set variables below or use a .env file
### ============================================================

@foundryEndpoint = {{$dotenv AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT}}
@foundryKey      = {{$dotenv AZURE_OPENAI_KEY}}
@searchEndpoint  = {{$dotenv AZURE_SEARCH_ENDPOINT}}
@searchKey       = {{$dotenv AZURE_SEARCH_KEY}}
@apimBase        = https://tva-workshop-apim.azure-api.net/tva-YOURNAME
@apimKey         = workshop-demo-key-2026
@backendLocal    = http://localhost:3001
@mcpLocal        = http://localhost:3002

### ============================================================
### SECTION 1 — Local Docker Services
### ============================================================

### 1a. TVA Backend Health Check
GET {{backendLocal}}/health

###

### 1b. TVA MCP Server Health Check
GET {{mcpLocal}}/health

###

### 1c. Query TVA Backend Directly
POST {{backendLocal}}/api/query
Content-Type: application/json
X-Api-Key: {{apimKey}}

{
  "query": "NERC CIP-007 patch management requirements",
  "top": 3
}

###

### ============================================================
### SECTION 2 — MCP Server Tools
### ============================================================

### 2a. List Available MCP Tools
POST {{mcpLocal}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "method": "tools/list",
  "params": {}
}

###

### 2b. Search TVA Documents
POST {{mcpLocal}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "search_tva_docs",
    "arguments": {
      "query": "nuclear plant safety temperature limits",
      "top": 2
    }
  }
}

###

### 2c. Get NERC Requirement
POST {{mcpLocal}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "get_nerc_requirement",
    "arguments": {
      "standard": "CIP-007"
    }
  }
}

###

### 2d. Check Compliance Status
POST {{mcpLocal}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "check_compliance_status",
    "arguments": {
      "standard": "CIP-010"
    }
  }
}

###

### 2e. List All Regulations
POST {{mcpLocal}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "list_regulations",
    "arguments": {}
  }
}

###

### ============================================================
### SECTION 3 — Azure APIM
### ============================================================

### 3a. Query via APIM (update suffix in @apimBase above)
POST {{apimBase}}/api/query
Content-Type: application/json
X-Api-Key: {{apimKey}}

{
  "query": "grid reliability performance targets",
  "top": 3
}

###

### ============================================================
### SECTION 4 — Azure OpenAI / AI Foundry
### ============================================================

### 4a. Direct Azure OpenAI — No RAG (baseline test)
POST {{foundryEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/gpt-4o/chat/completions?api-version=2024-05-01-preview
Content-Type: application/json
api-key: {{foundryKey}}

{
  "messages": [
    {"role": "system", "content": "You are a TVA compliance assistant."},
    {"role": "user", "content": "What are the NERC CIP-007 requirements?"}
  ],
  "max_tokens": 500
}

###

### 4b. Azure OpenAI WITH RAG — AI Search grounding
POST {{foundryEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/gpt-4o/chat/completions?api-version=2024-05-01-preview
Content-Type: application/json
api-key: {{foundryKey}}

{
  "messages": [
    {"role": "system", "content": "You are a TVA compliance assistant. Always cite your sources."},
    {"role": "user", "content": "Summarize TVA's NERC CIP compliance posture"}
  ],
  "data_sources": [
    {
      "type": "azure_search",
      "parameters": {
        "endpoint": "{{searchEndpoint}}",
        "index_name": "tva-knowledge-base",
        "authentication": {
          "type": "api_key",
          "key": "{{searchKey}}"
        }
      }
    }
  ],
  "max_tokens": 800
}

###

### 4c. Test File Upload (multipart — use curl for binary files)
# curl -X POST "{{foundryEndpoint}}/openai/deployments/gpt-4o/chat/completions?api-version=2024-05-01-preview" \
#   -H "api-key: YOUR_KEY" \
#   -F "file=@./docs/tva-sample.pdf" \
#   -F 'messages=[{"role":"user","content":"Summarize this document"}]'
